glauconite bed associated with several Zoophycos traces

Section 1 contains three green glaconitic horizons at 3,8, 36 cm.  Rare scattered sufides occur around 11 and 104-111 cm and a darker greenish grey interval at 0-36cm.  Three intervals of increased brown mottling (more moderate bioturbation) occur at roughly 36-47, 83-96, 112-119 cm, and appear to coincide with faint color changes between slightly lighter and darker intervals on decimeter scales.

Section 2 contains the most variation in mottling (inferred bioturbation) of all sections in Core 18H. There are more frequent sulfides from 37-52 cm. A transition from relatively more grey (0-64 cm) to lighter grey (64-83 cm) is coincident with increased brown mottles (61-74 cm). A bluer interval from 83-126 cm contains more distinct grey and then brown mottles than the rest of the core.  The transition between the bluer and the light grey at the end of the core (126-150 cm) is characterized by large burrows (Zoophycus and planolites). A green horizon occurs at 101 cm.

Brown (10Y 6/1) mottles with associated sulfide flecks at 16-19, 34-38, and 69-83 cm. Sparse faint lighter mottles and smaller brown blebs scattered throughout (bioturbation generally appears heavy).  Slightly greyer/green bed at 109.5-112cm and 1-cm thick darker green/black bed at 127 cm.

Faint brown (10Y 6/1) mottles scattered throughout and faint brown horizons at 26-27, 33-44, and 135 cm. Scatter concentrations of sulfides at 34, 49-54, 78-83 cm and low density scatter between 107-140 cm. Increased faint mottling (including light grey) at 37-55 and 118-145 cm, indicative of more moderate bioturbation.  Slightly bluer interval from 114-135 cm.

Rare, faint brown (10Y 6/1) mottles scattered throughout, with an interval of larger, more concentrated mottles from 50-63 cm. Sulfide horizons 36 and 102 cm, and burrow associated sulfide patches from 143-150 cm. Green glauconite horizons at 20, 42, and 45 cm, the first of which is associated with sulfides. Interval of increased mottling and sulfides from 50-63 cm.

Rare, faint brown mottles (10Y 6/1) througout; green horizons at 46 and 52 cm, scattered sulfides concentrated around 7-14 and 43-52 cm.  A darker blue grey interval from 93-111 cm characterizd by lighter grey mottles (top) and brown mottles (bottom).
Black sulfide blebs/mottles likely reflecting flow in stain the surface.
